cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on improving language understanding in social conversations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a method that involves machine learning models, which suggests that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of their approach on dialog act prediction and semantic role labeling, which could place it under cs.SD (Sound and Dialogue) as well. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of improving social dialog understanding, which could make it relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
